{{project_framing}}

**This is not a tracker.** See [CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md) for the operating contract that the AI assistant follows in this repo.

## Layout

- `intake/` — case context: journey, treatments, current state, constraints, diagnostics, open questions
- `treatments/` — what's been tried, what's current, candidates under exploration (gated until frontier scan complete), ruled out
- `causes/` — working hypotheses about etiology and refractoriness
- `mechanisms/` — pathophysiology deep dives, written when relevant
- `literature/` — paper notes, topic maps, saved searches, sources catalog
- `data/raw/` — exported tracker data
- `clinician/` — visit notes and pre-visit synthesis packets
- `notes/` — working notes, brainstorms
- `meta/` — operating definitions (standards), research methodology, frontier-scan gate, decisions log

## Privacy notice

This repository will accumulate personal health information. **Do not push it to a public remote** without an explicit redaction review. Even seemingly-innocuous notes can re-identify the patient by the combination of condition, region, and treatment history.

## First session

The first working session in this repo is the **frontier scan**. See `meta/frontier-scan-status.md` for the checklist. Treatment-candidate work is gated on its completion.
